            . I am shopman to Mr. H. Floyd, <rs id="t18230115-51-viclabel295" type="occupation">hosier</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230115-51-victim570 t18230115-51-viclabel295"></join>, of <placeName id="t18230115-51-crimeloc296">the Minories</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18230115-51-crimeloc296" type="placeName" value="the Minories"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18230115-51-crimeloc296" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230115-51-off293 t18230115-51-crimeloc296"></join>. On the 30th of December, about twelve o'clock, I was serving a customer, the prisoner came in with a boy about eighteen years old, who had a pair of skates, and asked for a cravat - he wished to have it out of a particular corner of the window, and while I was getting it, I saw the prisoner helping himself out of the other window. I saw a handkerchief on a line move; the boy did not buy the cravat; the prisoner ran out - I pursued, and took hold of him six doors off, and took a silk and a cotton handkerchief out of his hat; he said his mother gave him one of them. I can swear to one.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18230115-51-person572">
                  JOSEPH 
                  STONE
